    <unitdate datechar="creation" type="inclusive">circa 1890-1963</unitdate>
    <abstract id="aspace_881d304274418f8d0399a5644155f05c">Cigar bands and cigar box labels, most clearly marked with the brand and company of cigar, collected by Sidney P. Voice, vice-president of the Consolidated Lithographing Corporation in Brooklyn, which produced many of these items. The collection includes several salesman's sample books for New York lithographing companies.</abstract>
    <langmaterial id="aspace_b79d61d7c9106559f72109b3fbec0300">The documents in the collection are in English.</langmaterial>
  </did>
  <accessrestrict id="aspace_b959a395e4e5b749e722e7dd736ee7e6">
    <head>Access Restrictions</head>
<p>Open to qualified researchers by appointment only. To schedule an appointment, contact the Print Room Librarian at printroom@nyhistory.org.</p>  </accessrestrict>
  <acqinfo id="aspace_25c339770876db47f09945535141fc03">
    <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
<p>Gift of Sidney P. Voice, 1973, 1977, and 1983.</p>  </acqinfo>
  <arrangement id="aspace_bb8e77090cabe767b147757dac1f2c45">
    <head>Arrangement</head>
<p>The collection is organized by format: Cigar Bands, Cigar Box Labels, Cigar Edgings, and Registration Certificates.</p>  </arrangement>
  <bioghist id="aspace_0a7afd09504082a0f964c8d88b106b23">
    <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
<p>Sidney Voice was the vice-president of Consolidated Lithographing Corporation in Brooklyn.</p>  </bioghist>
  <prefercite id="aspace_c4ee1972a8562ab05f32debca6c9f49f">
