  <relatedmaterial id="aspace_1e4840eea10f6dd8006c090eb962c54b">
    <head>Related Materials</head>
<p>Additional cigar labels can be found in the <extref xlink:actuate="onRequest" xlink:href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/nyhs/landauer/">Bella C. Landauer Collection of Business and Advertising Ephemera (PR-031)</extref>, the <extref xlink:actuate="onRequest" xlink:href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/nyhs/ephemera/">Ephemera Collection (PR-264)</extref>, and the <extref xlink:actuate="onRequest" xlink:href="http://dlib.nyu.edu/findingaids/html/nyhs/pr392_karp/">Amie Karp Collection of Tobacciana (PR-392)</extref>. More cigar printing done by the Consolidated Lithographing Corp. can be found in the <extref xlink:actuate="onRequest" xlink:href="https://bobcat.library.nyu.edu/permalink/f/22u4kq/nyu_aleph001139020">Kane-Greenberg Collection of Progressive Proof Prints (PR-242)</extref>.</p>  </relatedmaterial>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_ee0c474430023afaffc2f6e3a7c9c711">
    <head>Scope and Contents</head>
<p>The Sidney Voice Collection of Cigar Bands spans the period from circa 1890 to circa 1963 and contains cigar bands, cigar box labels, and salesman's sample books for New York and Brooklyn lithographers. A few registration certificates for cigar brand names are also included. Cigar bands are housed loose, pasted onto boards, and pasted into albums.</p>  </scopecontent>
